Definition: a tendency to be negligent and uncaring
Example: he inherited his delinquency from his father; his derelictions were not really intended as crimes; his adolescent protest consisted of willful neglect of all his responsibilities
Synonyms: adj, all, guilty, delinquent, dereliction, willful_neglect, negligence, a, tendency, to, be, negligent, and, uncaring, he, inherited, his, from, father, derelictions, were, not, really, intended, as, crimes, adolescent, protest, consisted, of, willful, neglect, responsibilities
Category: noun.attribute
